# FootballPulse Conventions

- This repo uses `project.yml` with XcodeGen as the project source of truth.
- Keep the iPhone app modular: `App`, `Core`, `Features`, and `Shared` folders under `FootballPulse/Sources`.
- Never commit `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` or other real API credentials.
- Prefer keeping the app runnable in mock mode when external config is missing.
- Do not strip `FootballPulse/Info.plist`: keep localhost ATS exceptions, `UILaunchScreen`, and scene/orientation keys. `BackendBaseURL` is injected via `INFOPLIST_KEY_BackendBaseURL` in `project.yml` from `$(BACKEND_BASE_URL)` in xcconfig; after adding Swift files run `xcodegen generate`.
- Read and update `.cursor/memory/project-memory.md` when major architectural decisions change.
